00:02:51.479 --> 00:02:54.199
So pointblank is for data validation, obviously.

00:02:54.199 --> 00:02:56.479
And the workflow that we use inside this package

00:02:56.479 --> 00:02:58.919
is we create something called an agent.

00:02:58.919 --> 00:03:01.119
It's just a function called create agent.

00:03:01.119 --> 00:03:02.839
So that's the first thing you got to do.

00:03:02.839 --> 00:03:05.320
That's where you actually give the object your data,

00:03:05.320 --> 00:03:07.399
like the table you want to validate.

00:03:07.399 --> 00:03:08.600
OK, so that's very important.

00:03:08.600 --> 00:03:11.199
It's kind of like the first step.

00:03:11.199 --> 00:03:15.839
And then in the middle, there's as many functions

00:03:15.839 --> 00:03:18.320
as you want, this declaration of validation steps

00:03:18.320 --> 00:03:19.919
using validation functions.

00:03:19.919 --> 00:03:22.720
OK, the more you add, the more stringent

00:03:22.720 --> 00:03:27.360
that your validation process is going to go down.

00:03:27.360 --> 00:03:30.000
OK, and then finally, there's a third step,

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:31.279
the interrogation of the data.

00:03:31.279 --> 00:03:33.039
This is where the agent finally carries out

00:03:33.039 --> 00:03:34.080
the validation tasks.

00:03:34.080 --> 00:03:36.320
Up to that point, it just has the data,

00:03:36.320 --> 00:03:38.160
but it doesn't actually do anything with it.

00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:41.199
So you have to use this to sort of initiate the whole process.

00:03:44.080 --> 00:03:45.600
So let's actually run through this.

