00:06:42.040 --> 00:06:47.760
OK, two more, or three more, which begin with col is.

00:06:47.760 --> 00:06:53.320
So we're saying columns E and D are logical and numeric,

00:06:53.320 --> 00:06:55.239
respectively.

00:06:55.239 --> 00:06:59.160
And that columns B and F are character columns.

00:06:59.160 --> 00:07:01.600
OK, finally, for the last validation step,

00:07:01.600 --> 00:07:03.440
we have rows distinct.

00:07:03.440 --> 00:07:07.559
So in this one, we're saying that all the rows are unique.

00:07:08.519 --> 00:07:10.000
OK, those are our expectations.

00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:12.799
So we see in the actual output, though,

00:07:12.799 --> 00:07:14.959
it's kind of nice to see this because we sort of see

