I didn't go over everything.

00:09:41.280 --> 00:09:42.520
Basically, step is important.

00:09:42.520 --> 00:09:44.599
That's the column, the first column.

00:09:44.599 --> 00:09:46.599
Each time you use a validation function,

00:09:46.599 --> 00:09:48.559
it will make a new step.

00:09:48.559 --> 00:09:51.239
Sometimes one use of a validation function

00:09:51.239 --> 00:09:52.479
will make multiple steps.

00:09:52.479 --> 00:09:58.280
Say if you define multiple columns in a column type check,

00:09:58.280 --> 00:10:03.479
it will just expand to several rows or several steps.

00:10:03.479 --> 00:10:07.000
Columns, if there are column-based validation

00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:08.880
checks, this will become relevant,

00:10:08.880 --> 00:10:11.440
and there'll be names of target columns in there.

00:10:14.640 --> 00:10:16.919
Same goes for the values column.

00:10:16.919 --> 00:10:19.440
If there are any values associated with something,

00:10:19.440 --> 00:10:21.200
say, for instance, you're checking

00:10:21.200 --> 00:10:22.840
