are the calculations performed in the database, or is the data pulled locally first?

01:41:54.245 --> 01:41:59.245
Definitely the first one, in the database.

01:41:59.245 --> 01:42:04.245
We do everything with dbplyr,

01:42:04.245 --> 01:42:09.245
which is loaded at dplyr load time,

01:42:09.245 --> 01:42:14.245
and we don't purposefully collect any data before everything is summarized down

01:42:14.245 --> 01:42:19.245
into the final results.

01:42:19.245 --> 01:42:24.245
Oh, yes.

