01:44:50.245 --> 01:44:55.245
Probably non-tabular data and basically any data you do have in tables, which are things like list columns, doesn't really handle that.

01:44:55.245 --> 01:45:00.245
Unless you especially, and you can handle it yourself.

01:45:00.245 --> 01:45:05.245
I mean, you can do pretty much anything you want with that one function, which gives you carte blanche.

01:45:05.245 --> 01:45:10.245
Just write your own UDF, your own function to create a validation.

01:45:10.245 --> 01:45:15.245
As long as you give it the results that it expects, which is a list of, sorry,

01:45:15.245 --> 01:45:20.245
a vector of logicals or a table with a final column is logical.

01:45:20.245 --> 01:45:25.245
You can do pretty much whatever you want and whatever you can imagine in terms of validation.

01:45:25.245 --> 01:45:30.245
